The paper discusses security issues in wireless sensor networks, which is a subfield of computer networks and falls under the category of cs.NI (Networks and Internet Architecture). However, the paper specifically focuses on cognitive wireless sensor networks, which are networks that have the ability to adapt to their environment, making it likely that the paper also falls under the sub-categories of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper discusses defense mechanisms and open problems, which could fall under the sub-categories of cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
